article.description: James Batemon had 19 points as Loyola Marymount narrowly beat San Francisco 74-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Batemon leads Loyola Marymount past San Francisco 74-69
article.linkText: Batemon leads Loyola Marymount past San Francisco 74-69
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- James Batemon had 19 points as Loyola Marymount narrowly beat San Francisco 74-69 on Saturday. Eli Scott had 15 points for Loyola Marymount (20-10, 8-8 West Coast Conference). Frankie Ferrari had 13 points and eight assists for the Dons (21-9, 9-7). Jimbo Lull added 13 points. Dzmitry Ryuny had 12 points. The Lions and the Dons next take the floor in the West Coast Conference Tournament. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
